{{orphan|date=November 2016}}
'''Dafydd ap Phylip ap Rhys''' was a 16th century Welsh poet (probably from Llangyfelach, near [[Swansea]]). He may have been a member of a holy order. A [[cywydd]] in praise of [[Sir Rhys ap Thomas]] (q.v.) is thought to be his only surviving work. He is mentioned in the [[Iolo Morganwg manuscripts]], held by the [[National Library of Wales]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dafydd ap Phylip ap Rhys|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-DAFY-APP-1500.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=8 November 2016}}</ref>

