{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = His Excellency | name = Mathew Cheriankunnel | title = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kurnool|Bishop Emeritus of Kurnool]] | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kurnool|Catholic Diocese of Kurnool]] | term = 1988 - 1991 | predecessor = Joseph Rajappa | successor = Abraham Aruliah Somavarapa <!-- Orders --> | ordination = 28 April 1962 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1930|9|23}} | birth_place = [[Kadayanicad]] | death_date = | death_place = | previous_post = }}
'''Mathew Cheriankunnel''' (born 23 September 1930 in [[Kadayanicad]], [[India]]) is the emerit [[bishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kurnool]].
== Biography == Born on 23 September 1930 in Kadayanicad, he was ordained [[priest]] of [[Pontifical Institute for Foreign Missions|PIME]] on 28 April 1962.
He was appointed the first bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Nalgonda|Nalgonda]] on 31 May 1976, and receiving his episcopal consecration on 3 May 1977, from [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] [[Duraisamy Simon Lourdusamy]].
He was appointed [[coadjutor bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kurnool|Catholic Diocese of Kurnool]] on 22 December 1986, succeeding on 18 January 1988.
He left the diocese gouvernement for illness on 16 July 1991.
